In which release are sparse tensors supported in tf.data.Dataset? I have 1.4.0 and I'm getting the following error:

TypeError: Failed to convert object of type <class 'tensorflow.python.framework.sparse_tensor.SparseTensor'> to Tensor. Contents: SparseTensor(indices=Tensor("ParseSingleExample/Slice_Indices_label:0", shape=(?, 1), dtype=int64), values=Tensor("Cast_1:0", shape=(?,), dtype=int32), dense_shape=Tensor("ParseSingleExample/Squeeze_Shape_label:0", shape=(1,), dtype=int64)). Consider casting elements to a supported type.

```

Contents: SparseTensor(indices=Tensor("ParseSingleExample/Slice_Indices_label:0", shape=(?, 1), dtype=int64), values=Tensor("Cast_1:0", shape=(?,), dtype=int32), dense_shape=Tensor("ParseSingleExample/Squeeze_Shape_label:0", shape=(1,), dtype=int64)).
